dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:250000;  Projection: Lambert conical orthomorphic projection;  Map Type: lcgft;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series: Relief shown by contours, gradient tints, and spot heights.  Five classes of railways and five classes of roads are shown.  Covers area west from Krefeld to Rheda-Wiederbrück to the east, and north from Münster to Bergneustadt to the south. Dortmund roughly at center of sheet. Düsseldorf roughly at lower left corner of sheet.  Likely reprint of Sheet K 52, Düsseldorf by Army Map Service, U.S. Army from series originally issued in various editions by Geographical Section, General Staff, No. 4346.  Military grid.  Nord de Guerre Zone Grid ... Spheroid, Du Plessis..  Heights in metres..  Certain main spot heights are indicated by a white tab to improve legibility..  Cataloging agency's copy printed on verso of unrelated map, Sheet 9-O, Gourdon from series with title: France 1:100,000, A.M.S. M661 (G.S.G.S. 4249). First edition-AMS 2. Originally published Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1943-. Portion of unrelated map has overprint red X crossing out entirety of mapped area, as well as portions of legend.  IXA.  Includes legend, Incidence of grid letters diagrams, Convergence for corners of this sheet diagram, To give a grid reference on this sheet, Grid data: Nord de Guerre Grid, Index to adjoining sheets, index to corresponding 1:100,000 scale sheets, Conversion table, Authorities, and Glossary.  55/10-44/H/5079..
dct_isPartOf_sm: Field Maps of Colonel Roland T. Fenton
